---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Ethiopia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/ethiopia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Kenya for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kenya' },
  { title: 'Egypt for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/egypt' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'ethiopiaFit', header: 'Ethiopia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ETB$27,500-39,250/mo', ethiopiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ETB$32,200-46,000/mo', ethiopiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ETB$24,750-35,325/mo', ethiopiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ETB$23,000-32,850/mo', ethiopiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Awash, Nyala)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'ETB$5,000-15,000/mo', ethiopiaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'ETB$24,750-39,250', annual: 'ETB$297K-471K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'ETB$33,950-52,350', annual: 'ETB$407.4K-628.2K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'ETB$45,650-70,300', annual: 'ETB$547.8K-843.6K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'ETB$2,000-6,000/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'ETB$15,000-40,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Ethiopia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Ethiopia. Ancient history, unique culture, coffee origin, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Ethiopia"
  subheadline="Ethiopia offers ancient Christian history, unique calendar and cuisine, coffee origin, and diverse landscapes—Africa's only uncolonized nation with distinctive culture for adventurous retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/ethiopia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Ethiopia</h2>
  <p>
    Ethiopia offers ancient Orthodox Christian history (Lalibela rock churches), unique cuisine and culture, birthplace of coffee, and Africa's only uncolonized nation. For adventurous retirees seeking truly distinctive experience, Ethiopia provides unmatched historical and cultural depth.
  </p>

  <p>
    Addis Ababa is the capital with best healthcare and African Union headquarters. Lalibela has ancient rock churches. Gondar offers castles. Simien Mountains provide trekking. Most expats choose Addis for healthcare and services.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Dubai/Nairobi backup needed</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Amharic; English growing</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> ETB$40,000-80,000/month (~$700-1,400 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Highland pleasant; varied regions</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Ancient; unique; independent</li>
      <li><strong>Challenges:</strong> Different calendar, bureaucracy, internet limits</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Ethiopia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Ethiopia healthcare is limited—Korean Hospital and private clinics in Addis provide better care. Public system underfunded. Most complex cases evacuate to Dubai (4-hour flight) or Nairobi (2-hour flight). Medical tourism abroad common for serious conditions.
  </p>

  <p>
    Healthcare improving but from low base. International clinics serve expat community. Regional healthcare very basic. International insurance with strong evacuation coverage essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">International Evacuation Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Ethiopia requires international evacuation capability—Dubai and Nairobi are main destinations for complex care. Include Middle East and East Africa in coverage. Local care handles routine needs; international evacuation for serious conditions is essential.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Ethiopia has accessible e-visa:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist e-Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-90 days via e-visa. Simple online application. Most nationalities eligible.
  </p>

  <h3>Business Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For business activities. Multiple entry options available.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For longer stays. Various categories. Apply through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For business investment. Ethiopia encouraging foreign investment.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Ethiopia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Yellow fever vaccination required; insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Dubai/Nairobi coverage critical</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Ethiopia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with strong international evacuation coverage essential. Addis Ababa has some private options. Dubai and Nairobi provide specialist backup. Don't rely on local healthcare for serious conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Ethiopia, international evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Ethiopia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong global network, Dubai access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>International evacuation:</strong> Essential for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Middle East access:</strong> Dubai provides backup</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with international evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Ethiopia (ETB ~55 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Addis base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Dubai network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Routine care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Comprehensive evacuation:</strong> Don't cut this</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: AU/NGO Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month pension. Residence permit. Addis.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Middle East and Africa coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ETB$30,000/month (~$545). Development community; international backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: History Enthusiast, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,800/month pension. Tourist rotation. Exploring.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive with strong evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ETB$38,000/month (~$690). Cultural immersion; global backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Coffee Business, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month income. Business visa. Addis.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with comprehensive evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ETB$25,000/month (~$455). Business lifestyle; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Ethiopia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Varies by region—Addis generally safe. Conflict in some regions (check current situation). Tourist areas professionally managed. Ethnic tensions exist. Monitor travel advisories. Addis expat community thrives despite challenges.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Amharic?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful—Amharic is main language with unique script. English growing in business, educated class, healthcare. Learning basics highly valued. More challenging than other African destinations. Guides/interpreters available.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's unique about Ethiopia?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Everything—different calendar (7-8 years behind), unique time (6-hour offset), own alphabet, distinct cuisine (injera), coffee ceremonies, ancient Christianity, never colonized. Truly unique experience unlike anywhere else.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about internet/connectivity?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Limited—government controls internet, occasional shutdowns, slower speeds. Improving but not reliable. VPNs sometimes blocked. Plan for reduced connectivity. Different digital environment than most countries.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Ethiopia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Ethiopia authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
